THE GOSPEL ACCORDING TO ST MARK. By the Rev. G. F. MACLEAR‚ D.D. With 3Maps. 4s.6d.

“The Cambridge Greek Testament, of which Dr Maclear’s edition of the Gospel according to St Mark is a volume, certainly supplies a want. without pretending to compete with the leading commentaries, or to embody very much original research, it forms a most satisfactory introduction to the study of the New Testament in the original . . . Dr Maclear’s introduction contains all that is known of St Mark's life, with references to passages in the New Testament in which he is mentioned; an account of the circumstances in which the Gospel was composed, with an estimate of the influence of St Peter’s teaching upon St Mark: an excellent sketch of the special character- istics of this Gospel; an analysis. and a chapter on the text of the New Testament generally . . .
